Class NMSPacketReflection

java.lang.Object
com.github.yeetmanlord.reflection_api.NMSObjectReflection
com.github.yeetmanlord.reflection_api.packets.NMSPacketReflection
Direct Known Subclasses:
NMSChatPacketReflection, NMSEntityDestroyPacketReflection, NMSEntityEquipmentPacketReflection, NMSEntityPacketReflection, NMSEntityUsePacketReflection, NMSNamedEntitySpawnPacketReflection, NMSPacketPlayOutRelEntityMove, NMSPlayerInfoPacketReflection, NMSScoreboardTeamPacketReflection, NMSTitlePacketReflection
public class NMSPacketReflection extends NMSObjectReflection
This class is for reflecting NMS packets. It is a wrapper for the Packet class. It is used for sending packets to players in NMSPlayerConnectionReflection

    • NMSPacketReflection

      public NMSPacketReflection(PackageMapping mapping, String packetName, @Nullable Object... args)
      For reflecting NMS packets
      Parameters:
      mapping - The package mapping of the packet (Most of the time it's Mappings.PACKET_PLAY_PACKAGE_MAPPING)
      packetName - is the name of the packet you are reflecting although special packets have separate classes These classes are NMSScoreboardTeamPacketReflection, NMSEntityDestroyPacketReflection, NMSPlayerInfoPacketReflection NMSEntityPacketReflection NMSNamedEntitySpawnPacketReflection
      args - these are the arguments that the packet would normally take. If you use the wrong class there will be an error and the server will crash (For example you use a float instead of a byte) MAKE SURE TO CAST!! IMPORTANT NOTE: Passing nulls into this will not work if you have something null you wish to pass in to the constructor please use a different NMS Packet Reflection constructor.

      Parameters:

    • NMSPacketReflection

      public NMSPacketReflection(PackageMapping mapping, String packetName, Class<?>[] classes, Object... args)
      Parameters:
      packetName - The name of the packet to reflect
      classes - List of all classes that this packet's constructor uses. They are in the order that they appear in the wanted constructor.
      args - List of arguments to fill into the constructor. (In the order they appear in the constructor)
